The leading open source automation server, Jenkins provides hundreds of plugins to support building, deploying and automating any project.

webhooks:
webhooks are automated HTTP callbacks that allow external systems—most commonly version control systems like GitHub to notify Jenkins instantly when a specific event occurs. 
Instead of Jenkins periodically checking ("polling") for changes, the external system "pushes" a notification to Jenkins, triggering an immediate build or pipeline execution
